properties.areaDesc: Orange; Southern Lake County; Osceola; Inland Volusia; Northern Lake County; Seminole
properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 18 at 6:41AM EST by NWS Melbourne FL
properties.description:
Surface observations, satellite imagery and traffic cameras
indicated that patchy dense fog had formed in Lake, western
Orange, Seminole, interior Volusia and northwest Osceola counties.
The eastern edge of the fog will gradually erode toward the
northwest. This should linger the fog longest in north Lake and
northwest Volusia counties but even there, the fog should lift by
9 am. The fog will reduce visibilities below one half mile in
some locations.

Motorists should be prepared for rapidly changing visibilities.
When driving in dense fog, reduce your speed, use your low beam
headlights, and leave extra distance between your vehicle and the
one in front of you.

NWSheadline: Patchy Dense Fog Has Formed This Morning
